channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: Ohio GOP Senate candidate Moreno hits Brown on Inflation Reduction Act vote in ad that's part of $25M buy
item.description: Ohio Republican Bernie Moreno slammed Sen. Sherrod Brown for supporting the Inflation Reduction Act in a new ad shown to Fox News Digital in advance.

item.title: Trump rails against Biden's Helene response, compares it to border flop
item.description: Former President Donald Trump on Thursday ripped the Biden administration's response to Hurricane Helene, accusing the president of mishandling the crisis as badly as with the porous U.S. border.

item.title: Left-Wing President Snuffing Out a Source of Economic Hope for Hondurans
item.description: Xiomara Castro’s government is corruptly overturning a law that allowed for special economic-development zones.

item.title: Five GOP Reps. Demand Court Order Pennsylvania To Vet Overseas Voters’ Eligibility
item.description: Over 25,000 overseas absentee voting ballots have already been sent out, according to court papers.

item.title: Trump targets Biden, Harris over federal response to hurricane: 'Incompetently managed'
item.description: As President Biden spends a second straight day in the Southeast surveying storm damage from Hurricane Helene, Donald Trump blasts Biden and Kamala Harris over the federal government's relief efforts

item.title: Trump says Jack Smith's retooled case against him reeks of Democrats' election interference
item.description: Former President Donald Trump is accusing special counsel Jack Smith of election interference for filing a massive legal brief against him just five weeks before Election Day.

item.title: Israel Needs to Make Up Joe Biden’s Mind for Him
item.description: If the White House can’t decide what it wants in the Middle East, Israel must decide instead.

item.title: Biden-Harris Admin Claims FEMA Is Out Of Money. Here’s Where The Money Went
item.description: They've spent hundreds of millions of dollars on services for illegal immigrants as Americans struggle after Helene.

item.title: 'Reckless failure': Biden admin does nothing when leftists vandalize federal property, says watchdog
item.description: The Biden administration is failing to protect federal resources from damage or destruction during violent protests, according to conservative watchdog group Protect the Public's Trust.

item.title: Ex-Rep. Liz Cheney to campaign with Vice President Kamala Harris in Wisconsin
item.description: Former Rep. Liz Cheney will hit the campaign trail with Vice President Kamala Harris when the Democratic nominee stops Thursday in Wisconsin at the birthplace of the Republican Party.

item.title: Elections Officials Are Ready for November 5
item.description: As some on the left and the right challenge the electoral system, voters should know that it can meet the challenges of another presidential contest.

item.title: California AG Bonta Sued For ‘Chilling’ Protected Speech About Lifesaving Abortion Pill Reversal
item.description: ‘The Constitution protects Plaintiffs’ right to speak to the public and women about lawful medical treatments,’ the suit states.

item.title: Man convicted for dozens of threats against former Speaker McCarthy over Chinese balloons
item.description: A man from Montana was convicted by a federal jury this week on the charges of threatening former House Speaker Kevin McCarthy over the course of more than 100 phone calls.

item.title: Federal judge blocks California's deepfake anti-satire campaign law
item.description: A federal judge has halted California's new law targeting deepfake satire and parody videos, saying it likely tramples on the First Amendment.

item.title: Impound, Baby, Impound: How Trump Could Use Constitutional Authority to Cut Budget Bloat
item.description: An Elon Musk–headed commission would have a ready, if controversial, tool at its disposal.

item.title: Exclusive: Wyoming Elections Chief Warns Local Officials Of 2024 ‘Zuckbucks’ Interference
item.description: "I have serious concerns with CTCL's presence and with its solicitation of county clerks," Wyoming Secretary of State Chuck Gray wrote.

item.title: 5 key details in special counsel Jack Smith's Trump election case filing
item.description: Special counsel Jack Smith argues in a new court filing that former President Donald Trump is not immune from prosecution for his conduct immediately after the 2020 presidential election.

item.title: Tim Kaine, Hung Cao face off in only debate of campaign for U.S. Senate seat from Virginia
item.description: U.S. Sen. Tim Kaine of Virginia and Republican challenger Hung Cao sparred over issues from illegal immigration to tariffs on foreign goods Wednesday in their only debate of the campaign.

item.title: Lynnewood Hall: America’s Versailles Makes a Comeback
item.description: Long a mystery, close to ruin, the Gilded Age Philadelphia estate is being lovingly restored.
